<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFD34FEF351E8" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,276,675,701]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFD59FE9151BD" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,374,718,744]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Wingspan: 
<quantity id="3A7E9B3EFF92FFA46D74FD59FE9651BD" box="[284,369,718,744]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFD6DFD42506A" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Transverse lines: antemedial line well marked, black; postmedial line brown; both lines with a black spot on costa; subterminal line present but indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFCC7FDB2503F" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,597,848,874]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Reniform: indistinct, almost invisible.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFCECFE8150C0" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,358,891,917]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hindwing: brown</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFC31FDE45095" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,515,934,960]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Underside: unicolorous brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFC46FCE150BE" blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,774,977,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Abdomen: brown with a black crest on first segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFBB0FE865714" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,353,1063,1089]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFBC5FE235739" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,452,1106,1132]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ovipositor: quadrangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFBEAFC6357C2" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,900,1149,1175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Anterior apophyses: length equal to that of posterior apophyses.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFB3EFC215796" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,966,1189,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
8 
<superScript id="0AF39B93FF92FFA46CCDFB32FF5657E6" attach="left" box="[165,177,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: very narrow, ventrally fused with 7 
<superScript id="0AF39B93FF92FFA46F21FB32FCB257E6" attach="left" box="[841,853,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFB43FD75564C" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
7 
<superScript id="0AF39B93FF92FFA46CCDFB46FF56578A" attach="left" box="[165,177,1233,1247]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: heavily sclerotised, anteriorly with an irregular, triangular, apically narrow extension. Antrum: short, tapered, heavily sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFABDFB83563A" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ductus bursae: membranous, long, coiling by antrum; ostium and ductus bursae 2 X as long as corpus bursae. Appendix bursae: arising posteriorly from ductus bursae immediately after antrum.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFA17FE5056CF" blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,439,1408,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Corpus bursae: globular.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFFA41FE7B56A5" blockId="11.[151,971,1494,1564]" box="[151,412,1494,1520]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3936DBFF92FFA46CFFF995FC2C5549" blockId="11.[151,971,1494,1564]" box="[151,971,1538,1564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The female genitalia resemble those of 
<emphasis id="CFF2EAC9FF92FFA46E0DF995FD5A554E" box="[613,701,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="3A864D58FF92FFA46E0DF995FD5E554E" authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[613,697,1538,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tolpia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odor">T. odor</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
see under that species.
</paragraph>
